<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="691" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d691">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/18073</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Vice Consul <persName type="to">Blocker</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 7, 1916</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your May 7. Cooperate with Collector Customs and military commander,
                            Eagle Pass, in every way possible, in order to facilitate recovery of
                            bodies of murdered Americans and to provide such measure of safety as is
                            possible for the families of the victims. Keep Department fully and
                            promptly informed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>